# Q1) Write a program to create a DataFrame have E-commerce data and perform selection of row/column using `loc()` and `iloc()`

<br>

## CODE

```python
import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame({
    'OrderID': [1001, 1002, 1003, 1004, 1005],
    'Product': ['Laptop', 'Phone', 'Tablet', 'Headphones', 'Smartwatch'],
    'Price': [800, 500, 300, 150, 200],
    'Quantity': [1, 2, 3, 1, 4],
    'TotalAmount': [800, 1000, 900, 150, 800],
    'Customer': ['Anil', 'Ram', 'Shyam', 'Mukesh', 'Sita'],
})


print(df.loc[0:2, ['OrderID', 'Product', 'Price', 'Quantity', 'TotalAmount', 'Customer']])
print(df.iloc[0:3, 0:6])
```

|      1002 | Phone     |     500 |          2 |          1000 | Ram        |
|      1003 | Tablet    |     300 |          3 |           900 | Shyam      |

|   OrderID | Product   |   Price |   Quantity |   TotalAmount | Customer   |

# Q4) Write a program for combining DataFrames using `concat()`, `join()`, and `merge()` 

<br>

## CODE

```python
import pandas as pd

df1 = pd.DataFrame({
    'A': [1, 2, 3],
    'B': [4, 5, 6]
})
df2 = pd.DataFrame({
    'B': [7, 8, 9],
    'C': [4, 5, 6]
})

# concat (Joining vertically)
print(pd.concat([df1, df2], axis=0))


# join (Joining horizontally)
df1 = pd.DataFrame({
    'A': [1, 2, 3],
    'B': [11, 22, 33]
})
df2 = pd.DataFrame({
    'B': [11, 22, 33],
    'C': [111, 222, 333]
})
print(df1.join(df2, lsuffix='_df1', rsuffix='_df2'))

# merge (Joining on a common column)
print(pd.merge(df1, df2, on='B'))
```

<br>

## OUTPUT

|   A |   B |   C |
|----:|----:|----:|
|   1 |   4 | nan |
|   2 |   5 | nan |
|   3 |   6 | nan |
| nan |   7 |   4 |
| nan |   8 |   5 |
| nan |   9 |   6 |

|   A |   B_df1 |   B_df2 |   C |
|----:|--------:|--------:|----:|
|   1 |      11 |      11 | 111 |
|   2 |      22 |      22 | 222 |
|   3 |      33 |      33 | 333 |

|   A |   B |   C |
|----:|----:|----:|
|   1 |  11 | 111 |
|   2 |  22 | 222 |
|   3 |  33 | 333 |

# Q6) Write a program to implement Line plot, Dist plot, Lmplot, Count plot using Seaborn library

<br>

## CODE

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from seaborn import lineplot, displot, lmplot, countplot, load_dataset

df = load_dataset('iris')

# Line plot
lineplot(df, x='sepal_length', y='petal_length', hue='species')
plt.show()

# Distribution plot
displot(df, x='sepal_length')
plt.show()

# Linear model plot
lmplot(df, x='sepal_length', y='sepal_width', hue='species')

# Count plot

```

# Q8) Create a DataFrame ndf having Name, Gender, Position, City, Age, Projects. Write a program to summarize how many projects are being handled by each position for each city. Use `pivot()`

<br>

## CODE

```python
import pandas as pd

ndf = pd.DataFrame({
    'Name': ['A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E'],
    'Gender': ['M', 'F', 'M', 'F', 'M'],
    'Position': ['Manager', 'Developer', 'Manager', 'Developer', 'Tester'],
    'City': ['Delhi', 'Mumbai', 'Delhi', 'Mumbai', 'Delhi'],
    'Age': [30, 25, 35, 28, 22],
    'Projects': [5, 3, 4, 2, 1]
})

summary = ndf.pivot_table(index='City', columns='Position', values='Projects', aggfunc='sum', fill_value=0)
print(summary)

```

<br>

## OUTPUT

| City   |   Developer |   Manager |   Tester |
|:-------|------------:|----------:|---------:|
| Delhi  |           0 |         9 |        1 |
| Mumbai |           5 |         0 |        0 |

# Q11) Write a program to implement ANNOVA

<br>

## CODE

```python
from seaborn import load_dataset
from scipy.stats import f_oneway

df = load_dataset('iris')
grouped_data = [group['sepal_length'].values for name, group in df.groupby('species')]
f_statistic, p_value = f_oneway(*grouped_data)

print(f'ANOVA results for sepal length by species:')
print(f'F-statistic: {f_statistic}')
print(f'P-value: {p_value}')
```

<br>

## OUTPUT

    ANOVA results for sepal length by species:
    F-statistic: 119.26450218450468
    P-value: 1.6696691907693826e-31

# Q12) Write a program to show correlation between two randomly generated numbers

<br>

## CODE

```python
import pandas as pd
from random import randint

A = pd.Series([randint(1, 100) for _ in range(100)])
B = pd.Series([randint(1, 100) for _ in range(100)])
correlation = A.corr(B)
print(f'Correlation between two sets of random numbers: {correlation}')
```

<br>

## OUTPUT

    Correlation between two sets of random numbers: 0.09404602657803066

# Q13) Write a program to implement Covariance

<br>

## CODE

```python
import pandas as pd
from random import randint

A = pd.Series([randint(1, 100) for _ in range(100)])
B = pd.Series([randint(1, 100) for _ in range(100)])

covariance = A.cov(B)
print(f'Covariance between two sets of random numbers: {covariance}')
```

<br>

## OUTPUT

    Covariance between two sets of random numbers: 29.13131313131314

# Q14) Create a GUI based form for admission purpose for your college

<br>

## CODE

```python
import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import messagebox

def submit_form():
    name   = name_var.get()
    age    = age_var.get()
    gender = gender_var.get()
    course = course_var.get()
    email  = email_var.get()
    
    if not all([name, gender, course, email, age]):
        messagebox.showwarning('Incomplete', 'Please fill all fields')
    else:
        messagebox.showinfo('Success', f'Admission form submitted for {name}')

def clear_form():
    name_var.set('')
    age_var.set(0)
    gender_var.set('')
    course_var.set('')
    email_var.set('')

# Create main window
root = tk.Tk()
root.title('College Admission Form')
# root.geometry('400x400')

# Define variables
name_var   = tk.StringVar()
age_var    = tk.IntVar()
gender_var = tk.StringVar()
course_var = tk.StringVar()
email_var  = tk.StringVar()

# Title
tk.Label(root, text='Admission Form').pack(pady=10)

form_frame = tk.Frame(root)
form_frame.pack(pady=5)

# Name
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Full Name').grid(row=0, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
tk.Entry(form_frame, textvariable=name_var, width=30).grid(row=0, column=1, padx=10, pady=5)

# Age
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Age').grid(row=1, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
tk.Entry(form_frame, textvariable=age_var, width=30).grid(row=1, column=1, padx=10, pady=5)

# Gender (Radio Buttons)
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Gender').grid(row=2, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
gender_frame = tk.Frame(form_frame)
gender_frame.grid(row=2, column=1, pady=5)
tk.Radiobutton(gender_frame, text='Male',   variable=gender_var, value='Male').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(gender_frame, text='Female', variable=gender_var, value='Female').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(gender_frame, text='Other',  variable=gender_var, value='Other').pack(side='left')

# Course (Radio Buttons)
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Course').grid(row=3, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
course_frame = tk.Frame(form_frame)
course_frame.grid(row=3, column=1, pady=5)
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='BCA', variable=course_var, value='B.Tech').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='B.Tech', variable=course_var, value='B.Tech').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='BBA', variable=course_var, value='B.Sc').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='B.Com', variable=course_var, value='B.Com').pack(side='left')

# Email
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Email').grid(row=4, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
tk.Entry(form_frame, textvariable=email_var, width=30).grid(row=4, column=1, padx=10, pady=5)

# Buttons
btn_frame = tk.Frame(root)
btn_frame.pack(pady=15)

tk.Button(btn_frame, text='Submit', command=submit_form, width=12).pack(side='left', padx=10)
tk.Button(btn_frame, text='Clear', command=clear_form,   width=12).pack(side='right', padx=10)

root.mainloop()
```

<br>

# Q15) The created GUI based application form is to connected to a database and use insert query to enter data

<br>

## CODE

```python
import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import messagebox
import sqlite3

# Create/connect to database and table
conn = sqlite3.connect('admissions.db')
cursor = conn.cursor()
cursor.execute('''
    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS students (
        id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
        name TEXT,
        age INTEGER,
        gender TEXT,
        course TEXT,
        email TEXT
    )
''')


def submit_form():
    name   = name_var.get()
    age    = age_var.get()
    gender = gender_var.get()
    course = course_var.get()
    email  = email_var.get()
    
    if not all([name, gender, course, email, age]):
        messagebox.showwarning('Incomplete', 'Please fill all fields')
    else:
        try:
            cursor.execute('''
                INSERT INTO students (name, age, gender, course, email)
                VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)
            ''', (name, age, gender, course, email))
            conn.commit()
            messagebox.showinfo('Success', f'Data saved for {name}')
            clear_form()
        except Exception as e:
            messagebox.showerror('Error', f'Failed to insert into database:\n{e}')


def clear_form():
    name_var.set('')
    age_var.set(0)
    gender_var.set('')
    course_var.set('')
    email_var.set('')

# Create main window
root = tk.Tk()
root.title('College Admission Form')
# root.geometry('400x400')

# Define variables
name_var   = tk.StringVar()
age_var    = tk.IntVar()
gender_var = tk.StringVar()
course_var = tk.StringVar()
email_var  = tk.StringVar()

# Title
tk.Label(root, text='Admission Form').pack(pady=10)

form_frame = tk.Frame(root)
form_frame.pack(pady=5)

# Name
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Full Name').grid(row=0, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
tk.Entry(form_frame, textvariable=name_var, width=30).grid(row=0, column=1, padx=10, pady=5)

# Age
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Age').grid(row=1, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
tk.Entry(form_frame, textvariable=age_var, width=30).grid(row=1, column=1, padx=10, pady=5)

# Gender (Radio Buttons)
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Gender').grid(row=2, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
gender_frame = tk.Frame(form_frame)
gender_frame.grid(row=2, column=1, pady=5)
tk.Radiobutton(gender_frame, text='Male',   variable=gender_var, value='Male').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(gender_frame, text='Female', variable=gender_var, value='Female').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(gender_frame, text='Other',  variable=gender_var, value='Other').pack(side='left')

# Course (Radio Buttons)
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Course').grid(row=3, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
course_frame = tk.Frame(form_frame)
course_frame.grid(row=3, column=1, pady=5)
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='BCA',    variable=course_var, value='B.Tech').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='B.Tech', variable=course_var, value='B.Tech').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='BBA',    variable=course_var, value='B.Sc').pack(side='left')
tk.Radiobutton(course_frame, text='B.Com',  variable=course_var, value='B.Com').pack(side='left')

# Email
tk.Label(form_frame, text='Email').grid(row=4, column=0, sticky='e', padx=10, pady=5)
tk.Entry(form_frame, textvariable=email_var, width=30).grid(row=4, column=1, padx=10, pady=5)

# Buttons
btn_frame = tk.Frame(root)
btn_frame.pack(pady=15)

tk.Button(btn_frame, text='Submit', command=submit_form, width=12).pack(side='left', padx=10)
tk.Button(btn_frame, text='Clear', command=clear_form,   width=12).pack(side='right', padx=10)
```
